@startuml rollback
title Rollback: task state is version-controlled like code

skinparam monochrome false
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam rectangle {
    BackgroundColor #FAFAFA
    BorderColor #666
    RoundCorner 6
}

rectangle "Mon 09:00\n`bd create`\nbd-42: Fix auth bug" as T1 #D9EDFF
rectangle "Mon 14:00\n`bd update bd-42 in_progress`" as T2 #D9EDFF
rectangle "Tue 10:00\nBulk automation runs\n❌ wrong query\n**80 issues auto-closed**" as BAD #F5C2C7
rectangle "Tue 10:05\n`dolt log --oneline`\nsee the bad commit" as T4 #FFF8D6
rectangle "Tue 10:06\n`dolt reset --hard HEAD~1`\nreverts task DB" as T5 #C4E2AC
rectangle "Tue 10:07\n`bd dolt push`\nshares the recovery" as T6 #C4E2AC

T1 -right-> T2
T2 -right-> BAD
BAD -down-> T4
T4 -left-> T5
T5 -left-> T6

note bottom of BAD
  With Linear/Jira this is "call support,
  hope for the best." With beads it is
  one git-style command.
end note

@enduml
